otball biography\n|                name = Giorgos Valerianos\n|              image  = \n|            fullname = Georgios Valerianos\n|          birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1992|2|13}}\n|         birth_place = [[Athens]], Greece\n|              height = {{height|m=1.80}}\n|        currentclub  = [[Pafos FC|Pafos]]\n|         clubnumber  = 15\n|            position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Left-back]]\n| youthyears1 =  2005\u20132009 \n| youthclubs1 =  \n| years1 =  2010\u20132012| clubs1 = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]              | caps1 = 1  | goals1 = 0 \n| years2 =  2010\u20132011| clubs2 = \u2192 [[Thrasyvoulos]] (loan)                   | caps2 = 17 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 =  2012     | clubs3 = \u2192 [[A.O. Glyfada F.C.|Glyfada]] (loan)      | caps3 = 9  | goals3 = 1\n| years4 =  2012\u20132013| clubs4 = [[OFI Crete|OFI]]                           | caps4 = 1  | goals4 = 0\n| years5 =  2013\u20132014| clubs5 = [[Kavala F.C.|Kavala]]                      | caps5 = 17 | goals5 =  0\n| years6 = 2014\u20132015| clubs6 = [[Iraklis Thessaloniki F.C.|Iraklis]]        | caps6 = 13 | goals6 =  0\n| years7 = 2015\u20132016| clubs7 = [[Apollon Smyrnis F.C.|Apollon Smyrnis]]     | caps7 = 16 | goals7 =  1\n| years8 = 2016     | clubs8 = [[Platanias F.C.|Platanias]]                 | caps8 = 2  | goals8 = 0\n| years9 = 2016\u20132017| clubs9 = [[Apollon Smyrnis F.C.|Apollon Smyrnis]]     | caps9 = 26 | goals9 = 0\n| years10 = 2017\u20132019| clubs10 = [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]            | caps10 = 43 | goals10 = 0\n| years11 = 2019\u2013    | clubs11 = [[Pafos FC|Pafos]]                         | caps11 = 13 | goals11 = 0\n| years12 = 2019     | clubs12 = \u2192 [[Riga FC|Riga]] (loan)                  | caps12 =  2 | goals12 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2010\u20132012\n| nationalteam1 = [[Greece national under-19 football team|Greece U-19]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2019\u2013\n|  nationalteam2 = [[Greece national football team|Greece]]\n|  nationalcaps2 = 1\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| pcupdate = 01:26, 24 February 2020 (UTC).\n| ntupdate = {{date|2019-05-30}}\n}}\n'''Giorgos Valerianos''' ({{lang-el|\u0393\u03b9\u03ce\u03c1\u03b3\u03bf\u03c2 \u0392\u03b1\u03bb\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2}}; born 13 February 1992) is a Greek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left-back]] for [[Cypriot First Division]] club [[Pafos FC|Pafos]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.zougla.gr/sports/podosfero/article/sti-letonia-o-valerianos|title=\u03a3\u03b5 \u03bf\u03bc\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u039b\u03b5\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03bf \u0392\u03b1\u03bb\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2|website=www.zougla.gr|language=el|access-date=2019-07-14}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nGiorgos Valerianos began playing football with [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]. He is a very talented player and one of the best young players who were playing in Olympiacos U-21. He made 44 appearances for the youth team with four goals. Valerianos was first included in Olympiacos' first team in a league match against [[Panthrakikos F.C.|Panthrakikos]] on 11 April 2010, where he appeared as a second-half substitute.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=sports.e-go.gr|script-title=el:\u03a0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03bc\u03bf \u03c3\u03b5 \"\u039d\u03c4\u03ac\u03c1\u03bc\u03c0\u03b9\" \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u039b\u03bf\u03cd\u03b1 \u039b\u03bf\u03cd\u03b1|url=http://www.ethnos.gr/ethnosport/article.asp?catid=8140&subid=2&pubid=7610335|language=Greek|date=2010-04-09|title=Archived copy|access-date=4 May 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120313010101/http://www.ethnos.gr/ethnosport/article.asp?catid=8140&subid=2&pubid=7610335|archive-date=13 March 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 22 July 2014 he signed for [[Iraklis Thessaloniki F.C.|Iraklis]] in the [[Football League (Greece)|Greek Football League]].<ref>{{cite web |script-title=el:\u03a5\u03c0\u03ad\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c8\u03b5 \u03bf \u0392\u03b1\u03bb\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2 |accessdate=22 July 2014 |date=22 July 2014 |language=Greek |publisher=Iraklis FC |url=http://www.fciraklis.gr/nea/press/item/990-%CF%85%CF%80%CE%AD%CE%B3%CF%81%CE%B1%CF%88%CE%B5-%CE%BF-%CE%B2%CE%B1%CE%BB%CE%B5%CF%81%CE%B9%CE%AC%CE%BD%CE%BF%CF%82 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140730065453/http://www.fciraklis.gr/nea/press/item/990-%CF%85%CF%80%CE%AD%CE%B3%CF%81%CE%B1%CF%88%CE%B5-%CE%BF-%CE%B2%CE%B1%CE%BB%CE%B5%CF%81%CE%B9%CE%AC%CE%BD%CE%BF%CF%82 |archivedate=30 July 2014}}</ref> Valerianos debuted for Iraklis in a [[Greek Football Cup|cup]] match against [[Lamia F.C.|Lamia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bluearena.gr/%CF%80%CE%BF%CE%B4%CF%8C%CF%83%CF%86%CE%B1%CE%B9%CF%81%CE%BF/%CF%80%CE%BF%CE%B4%CF%8C%CF%83%CF%86%CE%B1%CE%B9%CF%81%CE%BF-%CE%B7%CF%81%CE%B1%CE%BA%CE%BB%CE%AE%CF%82/iraklis-lamia-0-0-1/|script-title=el:\u0398\u03b5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u03be\u03b5\u03ba\u03af\u03bd\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03bd\u03af\u03ba\u03b7 (1-0)|publisher=bluearena.gr|language=Greek|date=29 August 2014|accessdate=3 September 2014}}</ref> \nOn 12 August 2015, he signed a contract with second tier club [[Apollon Smyrni F.C.|Apollon Smyrnis]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fcapollon.gr/news/genika-nea/39/@2465.aspx?returnpage=%2fnews%2fgenika-nea%2f39.aspx%3fpage%3d0 |title=\u03a0\u03b1\u03af\u03ba\u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0391\u03c0\u03cc\u03bb\u03bb\u03c9\u03bd\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03bf \u0392\u03b1\u03bb\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2 |publisher=Apollon Smyrni FC |date=12 August 2015 |accessdate=23 August 2015 |language=Greek |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304030238/http://www.fcapollon.gr/news/genika-nea/39/@2465.aspx?returnpage=%2Fnews%2Fgenika-nea%2F39.aspx%3Fpage%3D0 |archivedate=4 March 2016}}</ref> On 29 January 2016, he solved his contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/apollonon-smirnis/telos-o-valerianos.3882328.html| title= \"\u03a4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2\" \u03bf \u0392\u03b1\u03bb\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2 | publisher=sport24.gr| date=29 January 2016| language=Greek}}</ref>\n\nThe 27-year-old left back can be considered as somewhat of a journeyman despite his age as on July 2017, signed with [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]] that officially announced his acquisition.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Aris/oi-prwtes-eksi-metagrafes-toy-arh.4780215.html |title=\u039f\u03b9 \u03c0\u03c1\u03ce\u03c4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03ad\u03be\u03b9 \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c6\u03ad\u03c2 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0386\u03c1\u03b7 |publisher=sport24.gr |date=25 July 2017}}</ref> His path to the top has been chequered and he has had to do it the hard way, meaning a lot of resilience was needed. Even [[2018\u201319 Superleague Greece|this season]] at Aris, he has been a squad player that has been rotated in and out of the team.\n\nOn 1 July 2019, after two years with Aris, Valerianos signed a three years' contract with Cypriot club [[Pafos FC|Pafos]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.sport24.gr/football/EllinesExoterikou/sthn-pafo-o-valerianos.5549746.html | title= \u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a0\u03ac\u03c6\u03bf \u03bf \u0392\u03b1\u03bb\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2 | publisher=sport24.gr| date=1 July 2019| language=Greek}}</ref> On 4 July 2019, the international back will have an intermediary station in his career after being loaned to [[Riga FC|Riga]], a Latvian football club, which owns the same property status as [[Pafos FC|Pafos]]. According to sources the borrowing will take just a month for the international left back in order to help the club for the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Europa League|2019\u201320 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.makthes.gr/apo-tin-pafo-sti-letonia-o-valerianos-226042 | title= \u0391\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a0\u03ac\u03c6\u03bf \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u039b\u03b5\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd\u03af\u03b1 \u03bf \u0392\u03b1\u03bb\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2 | publisher=makthes.gr| date=4 July 2019| language=Greek}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nOn 19 March 2019, Greece head coach [[Angelos Anastasiadis]] announced the first call up of Valerianos for the match against [[Liechtenstein national football team|Liechtenstein]] and [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] for [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=contra.gr |script-title=el:\u0397 \u03bb\u03bf\u03b3\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03c9 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03b9\u03c2 \u03ba\u03bb\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 \u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03b9\u03ac\u03b4\u03b7 |url=https://www.contra.gr/Soccer/Hellas/National-Greece/logiki-pisw-klhseis-anastasiadh.5467275.html |language=Greek|date=19 March 2019}}</ref> He made his debut on 30 May 2019, in a friendly against Turkey, as a starter.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=540122|title=Turkey v Greece game report|date=30 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|23 February 2020}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"80%\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=2|League\n!colspan=2|Cup\n!colspan=2|Continental\n!colspan=2|Other\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|[[2009\u201310 Superleague Greece|2009\u201310]]\n|1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||1||0\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Superleague Greece|2011\u201312]]\n|0||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||1||0\n|-\n!Total\n!1!!0!!1!!0!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!2!!0\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Thrasyvou