2, 1870\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Illinois|Illinois]] ====\n* {{ushr|Illinois|1|1}}. [[Norman B. Judd]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Illinois|2|2}}. [[John F. Farnsworth]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Illinois|3|3}}. [[Elihu B. Washburne]] (R), until March 6, 1869\n** [[Horatio C. Burchard]] (R), from December 6, 1869\n* {{ushr|Illinois|4|4}}. [[John B. Hawley]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Illinois|5|5}}. [[Ebon C. Ingersoll]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Illinois|6|6}}. [[Burton C. Cook]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Illinois|7|7}}. [[Jesse H. Moore]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Illinois|8|8}}. [[Shelby Moore Cullom|Shelby M. Cullom]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Illinois|9|9}}. [[Thompson W. McNeely]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Illinois|10|10}}. [[Albert G. Burr]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Illinois|11|11}}. [[Samuel S. Marshall]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Illinois|12|12}}. [[John B. Hay]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Illinois|13|13}}. [[John M. Crebs]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Illinois|AL|At-large}}. [[John A. Logan]] (R), until March 3, 1871\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Indiana|Indiana]] ====\n* {{ushr|Indiana|1|1}}. [[William E. Niblack]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Indiana|2|2}}. [[Michael C. Kerr]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Indiana|3|3}}. [[William S. Holman]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Indiana|4|4}}. [[George Washington Julian|George W. Julian]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Indiana|5|5}}. [[John Coburn (Indiana)|John Coburn]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Indiana|6|6}}. [[Daniel W. Voorhees]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Indiana|7|7}}. [[Godlove Stein Orth|Godlove S. Orth]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Indiana|8|8}}. [[James Noble Tyner|James N. Tyner]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Indiana|9|9}}. [[John P. C. Shanks]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Indiana|10|10}}. [[William Williams (Indiana)|William Williams]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Indiana|11|11}}. [[Jasper Packard]] (R)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Iowa|Iowa]] ====\n* {{ushr|Iowa|1|1}}. [[George W. McCrary]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Iowa|2|2}}. [[William Smyth (congressman)|William Smyth]] (R), until September 30, 1870\n** [[William P. Wolf]] (R), from December 6, 1870\n* {{ushr|Iowa|3|3}}. [[William B. Allison]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Iowa|4|4}}. [[Wi