]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Maryland|5|5}}. [[Frederick Stone]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Massachusetts|Massachusetts]] ====\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|1|1}}. [[James Buffington]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|2|2}}. [[Oakes Ames]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|3|3}}. [[Ginery Twichell]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|4|4}}. [[Samuel Hooper]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|5|5}}. [[Benjamin Butler (politician)|Benjamin F. Butler]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|6|6}}. [[Nathaniel Prentice Banks|Nathaniel P. Banks]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|7|7}}. [[George S. Boutwell]] (R), until March 12, 1869\n** [[George M. Brooks]] (R), from November 2, 1869\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|8|8}}. [[George Frisbie Hoar|George F. Hoar]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|9|9}}. [[William B. Washburn]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|10|10}}. [[Henry L. Dawes]] (R)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Michigan|Michigan]] ====\n* {{ushr|Michigan|1|1}}. [[Fernando C. Beaman]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Michigan|2|2}}. [[William L. Stoughton]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Michigan|3|3}}. [[Austin Blair]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Michigan|4|4}}. [[Thomas W. Ferry]] (R), until March 3, 1871\n* {{ushr|Michigan|5|5}}. [[Omar D. Conger]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Michigan|6|6}}. [[Randolph Strickland]] (R)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Minnesota|Minnesota]] ====\n* {{ushr|Minnesota|1|1}}. [[Morton S. Wilkinson]] (R)\n* {{ushr|Minnesota|2|2}}. [[Eugene McLanahan Wilson|Eugene M. Wilson]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Mississippi|Mississippi]] ====\n* {{ushr|Mississippi|1|1}}. [[George E. Harris]] (R), from February 23, 1870\n* {{ushr|Mississippi|2|2}}. [[Joseph L. Morphis]] (R), from February 23, 1870\n* {{ushr|Mississippi|3|3}}. [[Henry W. Barry]] (R), from April 8, 1870\n* {{ushr|Mississippi|4|4}}. [[George C. McKee]] (R), from February 23, 1870\n* {{ushr|Mississippi|5|5}}. [[Legrand W. Perce]] (R), from February 23, 1870\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Missouri|Mi