cratic}} | [[George Woodward Greene|George W. Greene]] (D)\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Lost contested election February 17, 1870\n| nowrap {{party shading/Republican}} | [[Charles Van Wyck]] (R)\n| February 17, 1870\n|-\n| {{ushr|South Carolina|1|South Carolina 1st}}\n| nowrap {{party shading/Republican}} | [[Benjamin Franklin Whittemore|Benjamin F. Whittemore]] (R)\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Resigned February 24, 1870, pending an investigation of certain appointments to the US Military and Naval Academies\n| nowrap {{party shading/Republican}} | [[Joseph Rainey]] (R)\n| December 12, 1870\n|-\n| {{ushr|Kentucky|3|Kentucky 3rd}}\n| nowrap {{party shading/Democratic}} | [[Jacob Golladay]] (D)\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Resigned February 28, 1870\n| nowrap {{party shading/Democratic}} | [[Joseph Horace Lewis|Joseph H. Lewis]] (D)\n| May 10, 1870\n|-\n| {{ushr|North Carolina|4|North Carolina 4th}}\n| nowrap {{party shading/Republican}} | [[John T. Deweese]] (R)\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Resigned February 28, 1870, pending an investigation of certain appointments to the US Military and Naval Academies\n| nowrap {{party shading/Democratic}} | [[John Manning, Jr.]] (D)\n| December 7, 1870\n|-\n| {{ushr|Pennsylvania|5|Pennsylvania 5th}}\n| nowrap {{party shading/Democratic}} | [[John Roberts Reading|John R. Reading]] (D)\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Lost contested election April 13, 1870\n| nowrap {{party shading/Republican}} | [[Caleb Newbold Taylor|Caleb N. Taylor]] (R)\n| April 13, 1870\n|-\n| {{ushr|North Carolina|2|North Carolina 2nd}}\n| nowrap {{party shading/Republican}} | [[David Heaton]] (R)\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Died June 25, 1870\n| nowrap {{party shading/Republican}} | [[Joseph Dixon (North Carolina)|Joseph Dixon]] (R)\n| December 5, 1870\n|-\n| {{ushr|New York|28|New York 28th}}\n| nowrap {{party shading/Republican}} | [[Noah Davis]] (R)\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Resigned July 15, 1870, before being appointed [[U.S. Attorney for the Southern 